fields.name: Authorization
fields.description: The sender authorization information.

fields.name: Caller
fields.description: the email address of the user who has performed the operation, the UPN claim or SPN claim based on availability.

fields.name: Category
fields.description: the event category.

fields.name: Claims
fields.description: key value pairs to identify ARM permissions.

fields.name: CorrelationId
fields.description: the correlation Id, usually a GUID in the string format. The correlation Id is shared among the events that belong to the same uber operation.

fields.name: Description
fields.description: the description of the event.

fields.name: EventDataId
fields.description: the event data Id. This is a unique identifier for an event.

fields.name: EventName
fields.description: the event name. This value should not be confused with OperationName. For practical purposes, OperationName might be more appealing to end users.

fields.name: EventTimestamp
fields.description: the timestamp of when the event was generated by the Azure service processing the request corresponding the event. It in ISO 8601 format.

fields.name: HTTPRequest
fields.description: the HTTP request info. Usually includes the 'clientRequestId', 'clientIpAddress' (IP address of the user who initiated the event) and 'method' (HTTP method e.g. PUT).

fields.name: Id
fields.description: the Id of this event as required by ARM for RBAC. It contains the EventDataID and a timestamp information.

fields.name: Level
fields.description: the event level

fields.name: OperationId
fields.description: It is usually a GUID shared among the events corresponding to single operation. This value should not be confused with EventName.

fields.name: OperationName
fields.description: the operation name.

fields.name: Properties
fields.description: the set of <Key, Value> pairs (usually a Dictionary<String, String>) that includes details about the event.

fields.name: ResourceGroupName
fields.description: the resource group name of the impacted resource.

fields.name: ResourceId
fields.description: the resource uri that uniquely identifies the resource that caused this event.

fields.name: ResourceProviderName
fields.description: the resource provider name of the impacted resource.

fields.name: ResourceType
fields.description: the resource type

fields.name: Status
fields.description: a string describing the status of the operation. Some typical values are: Started, In progress, Succeeded, Failed, Resolved.

fields.name: SubStatus
fields.description: the event sub status. Most of the time, when included, this captures the HTTP status code of the REST call. Common values are: OK (HTTP Status Code: 200), Created (HTTP Status Code: 201), Accepted (HTTP Status Code: 202), No Content (HTTP Status Code: 204), Bad Request(HTTP Status Code: 400), Not Found (HTTP Status Code: 404), Conflict (HTTP Status Code: 409), Internal Server Error (HTTP Status Code: 500), Service Unavailable (HTTP Status Code:503), Gateway Timeout (HTTP Status Code: 504)

fields.name: SubmissionTimestamp
fields.description: the timestamp of when the event became available for querying via this API. It is in ISO 8601 format. This value should not be confused eventTimestamp. As there might be a delay between the occurrence time of the event, and the time that the event is submitted to the Azure logging infrastructure.

fields.name: SubscriptionId
fields.description: the Azure subscription Id usually a GUID.

fields.name: TenantId
fields.description: the Azure tenant Id
